p: For CDV, the probability of epidemic fadeout was always very high, with medians >96% across all vaccination levels, vaccination distributions, and fox densities ( Fig 5A and 5B and S5 Table). Depending on the model treatment, fadeout occurred due to a lack of susceptible foxes either locally (with minimal fox infections) or after the disease spread through the entire fox population (infecting most foxes on the island). This bimodal distribution of model outcomes is reflected in the large IQRs in the percentage of infected foxes (Figs 5C and 5D and S2 and S5 Table). Many model treatments have large IQRs spanning almost the entire range of susceptible foxes (ex. 0 âˆ’ 90% of foxes infected with 10% vaccination) while the median values tend to be extremely high or very low ( Fig 5C and 5D and S5 Table).
